also be changed during runtime.

comments.message: Uploaded patch set 1.

I guess the config_client application can be dropped. You didn't even added it to the Makefile. A better alternative for quick tests is IBus python bindings, which provide much easier API.

In fedora, the package that installs the bindings is ibus-pygtk2.

subject: wkb-ibus: Fix repeatly create ibus-daemon.
commitMessage:
wkb-ibus: Fix repeatly create ibus-daemon.

It is possible that the ibus-daemon is up but weekeyboard can't
get anything from it. In this case, weekeyboard will always create
a new ibus-daemon. This patch fixes it.

Origin: upstream/e69bf40da41d2ee297854ccfef019432507f9752

Signed-off-by: Alex Wu <zhiwen.wu@linux.intel.com>

subject: wkb-ibus: Fix repeatly create ibus-daemon.
commitMessage:
wkb-ibus: Fix repeatly create ibus-daemon.

It is possible that the ibus-daemon is up but weekeyboard can't
get anything from it. In this case, weekeyboard will always create
a new ibus-daemon. This patch fix it.

Change-Id: I30a16c8e3048775b3709fbf8da671ca4fb1c509a
Signed-off-by: Alex Wu <zhiwen.wu@linux.intel.com>
